Renovation of Great Hall of the People Approaches End 
The newly completed renovation project of the Mongolia Hall at
Beijing's Great Hall of the People, has been checked and officially
accepted. It brings closer the end to overall renovation of the famous
building by Tiananmen Square.
An official responsible says that the overall renovation of the Great
Hall of the People has combined local features with the characteristics
of the time, and meanwhile, upgraded facilities for fire safety,
sewage, electricity, as well as air conditioning.
According to the official, the completed halls are all characterized by
their own local features, and all the materials used in the renovation
work were first class.
Construction of the Hong Kong Hall, covering 700-plus square meters,
has also finished the its major structure phase, and is now in the
process of being decorated.
